!! Module overview

|!Module |!Type |!Purpose |
|`startup.js` |startup |Auto-detection, re-parse, save pipeline patches |
|`deserializer.js` |tiddlerdeserializer |Parses YAML frontmatter from `.md` content |
|`parser.js` |parser |Renders `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` as markdown (strips frontmatter) |
|`yaml.js` |library |YAML parse/serialize (tags and list as arrays) |

!! Boot sequence

# TiddlyWiki boot scans `tiddlers/` — `.md` files without `.meta` get absolute filepath as title
# `startup.js` runs (`after: load-modules`, `before: startup, filesystem-watcher`)
# Registers `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` content type
# ''Pass 1'' — scans `boot.files` for `.md` files with `---` frontmatter pattern
# Suppresses `enqueueTiddlerEvent` (prevents syncer interference)
# Re-deserializes each file, determines title, replaces tiddler in wiki store
# Restores `enqueueTiddlerEvent`
# ''Pass 2'' — scans wiki tiddlers not in `boot.files` (loaded via `tiddlywiki.files`)
# Re-parses frontmatter, keeps existing title
# Syncer starts with correct state — no spurious file operations

!! Title derivation (Pass 1)

Priority order for each re-parsed tiddler:

# ''Frontmatter `title`'' — if YAML frontmatter contains a `title` field, use it
# ''Existing clean title'' — if boot title is not an absolute path (e.g., set by `tiddlywiki.files`), keep it
# ''Filepath-derived'' — for absolute-path titles: compute relative path from tiddlers dir, strip `.md`, replace `path.sep` with `/`

!! Save pipeline patches

The startup module patches three functions:

* `generateTiddlerFileInfo` — forces `.md` extension and `application/x-tiddler-frontmatter` disk type for `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` tiddlers
* `saveTiddlerToFile` — serializes as `---\nYAML\n---\ntext` instead of standard TW format; cleans orphaned `.meta` files
* `saveTiddlerToFileSync` — synchronous variant of the above

